## Stack: Node.js 20 + Express 5 + TypeScript

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| Runtime | Node.js 20 LTS |
| Framework | Express 5 |
| Language | TypeScript strict mode |
| Validation | Zod (body, query, params) |
| Logging | Pino + `pino-http` |
| ORM | Prisma 6 or raw `pg` (agent chooses per repo) |
| Testing | Jest + supertest |
| Build | `tsc --noEmit`; dev with `ts-node-dev` or `tsx` |

### Conventions

- **Express 5 handles async errors natively.** Do NOT install or import `express-async-errors` — a thrown promise from an async handler propagates to the error middleware on its own.
- **Validate every input with Zod** at the route boundary (body, query, params). Never trust `req.*` downstream of a route without a parsed type.
- **Never throw raw strings.** Throw a typed `AppError` (or subclass) so the central error middleware can map status + message safely.
- **From middleware, call `next(err)`** to forward errors; do not call `res.status().send()` for errors inside business middleware.
- **One central error middleware** with the `(err, req, res, next)` 4-arg signature, registered last in `app.ts`.
- **Type-check before declaring done:** `npm run build` (or `tsc --noEmit`) and `npm test` must both pass.

### Common commands

```bash
npm run dev          # ts-node-dev / tsx watch
npm run build        # tsc --noEmit (type-check) + compile
npm start            # node dist/index.js
npm test             # jest + supertest
npm run lint         # eslint
```
